[SN]TITLE[SN]
Would you watch TV on your hand?

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Do you love watching TV? Well, how do you fancy being able to watch it on your body?

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
11 April 2017 Last updated at 12:20 BST
Scientists from the University of Tokyo have developed a material that could allow you to do just that one day.
The thin 'e-skin' allows whoever is wearing it to have a digital display on their body.
It's 10 times thinner than normal skin and surprisingly strong.
Whitney's been finding out more.
